WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.583
<b>[MUSIC]</b>

2
00:00:05.958 --> 00:00:07.583
<b>As you start your treatment, you may</b>

3
00:00:07.583 --> 00:00:09.625
<b>wonder what you will be doing over the</b>

4
00:00:09.625 --> 00:00:11.000
<b>coming weeks of this course.</b>

5
00:00:11.916 --> 00:00:14.458
<b>So let's look at the overall plan for our</b>

6
00:00:14.458 --> 00:00:16.833
<b>time together, which has been carefully</b>

7
00:00:16.833 --> 00:00:17.791
<b>designed to best</b>

8
00:00:17.791 --> 00:00:20.125
<b>support your emotional needs.</b>

9
00:00:21.458 --> 00:00:23.416
<b>We'll present this course as a walk</b>

10
00:00:23.416 --> 00:00:26.250
<b>through a garden, divided into different</b>

11
00:00:26.250 --> 00:00:27.666
<b>areas that represent</b>

12
00:00:27.666 --> 00:00:29.375
<b>different parts of your therapy.</b>

13
00:00:30.916 --> 00:00:32.666
<b>We've used the metaphor of a garden</b>

14
00:00:32.666 --> 00:00:35.916
<b>because emotions are natural, and we will</b>

15
00:00:35.916 --> 00:00:38.583
<b>work with your emotions in a similar way</b>

16
00:00:38.583 --> 00:00:40.333
<b>that a gardener works with plants,</b>

17
00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.875
<b>not disliking them or ignoring them, but</b>

18
00:00:43.875 --> 00:00:46.875
<b>understanding what the plant is, deciding</b>

19
00:00:46.875 --> 00:00:48.916
<b>if it's in the right place in the garden,</b>

20
00:00:49.708 --> 00:00:52.333
<b>nurturing it, and most of all,</b>

21
00:00:52.708 --> 00:00:54.750
<b>appreciating it for what it does.</b>

22
00:00:56.375 --> 00:00:58.833
<b>In this course, we'll use a city to</b>

23
00:00:58.833 --> 00:01:00.875
<b>represent the world in which you live,</b>

24
00:01:01.416 --> 00:01:03.291
<b>the roar of traffic, the glow of lights,</b>

25
00:01:03.708 --> 00:01:06.250
<b>the constant activity, chatter, laughter,</b>

26
00:01:06.250 --> 00:01:08.000
<b>music and shouts of the</b>

27
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:09.250
<b>people who live there.</b>

28
00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:12.916
<b>It's a place where events and situations</b>

29
00:01:12.916 --> 00:01:14.208
<b>trigger our</b>

30
00:01:14.208 --> 00:01:16.791
<b>overwhelming, difficult emotions.</b>

31
00:01:18.375 --> 00:01:20.250
<b>But in the middle of all of these</b>

32
00:01:20.250 --> 00:01:23.375
<b>distractions, we find the quiet, safe</b>

33
00:01:23.375 --> 00:01:27.708
<b>haven that is our emotion garden, a safe</b>

34
00:01:27.708 --> 00:01:30.083
<b>space where we can explore</b>

35
00:01:30.083 --> 00:01:32.333
<b>and work with those emotions.</b>

36
00:01:34.125 --> 00:01:36.250
<b>We begin in the first area of the garden</b>

37
00:01:36.250 --> 00:01:39.041
<b>with setting a goal for positive change</b>

38
00:01:39.041 --> 00:01:41.291
<b>in your life with your emotions.</b>

39
00:01:42.583 --> 00:01:45.750
<b>Here, we are planting a seed of how life</b>

40
00:01:45.750 --> 00:01:48.125
<b>could be if you lived alongside your</b>

41
00:01:48.125 --> 00:01:49.458
<b>emotions more comfortably.</b>

42
00:01:52.625 --> 00:01:54.458
<b>Next, we move to the part of the garden</b>

43
00:01:54.458 --> 00:01:56.875
<b>where you learn about your emotions.</b>

44
00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:00.041
<b>We'll see there are four parts to an</b>

45
00:02:00.041 --> 00:02:04.000
<b>emotional response, how we feel, what we</b>

46
00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:06.625
<b>think, the physical sensations we</b>

47
00:02:06.625 --> 00:02:09.541
<b>experience in our body, and an immediate</b>

48
00:02:09.541 --> 00:02:12.250
<b>urge to behave in a particular way.</b>

49
00:02:13.833 --> 00:02:15.833
<b>This understanding is key to moving</b>

50
00:02:15.833 --> 00:02:16.750
<b>forward with our</b>

51
00:02:16.750 --> 00:02:18.166
<b>treatment more effectively.</b>

52
00:02:19.625 --> 00:02:21.583
<b>You'll also learn about why humans</b>

53
00:02:21.583 --> 00:02:24.875
<b>evolved to have emotions and how you can</b>

54
00:02:24.875 --> 00:02:27.291
<b>better use the information your emotions</b>

55
00:02:27.291 --> 00:02:29.833
<b>are giving you to improve your life.</b>

56
00:02:32.041 --> 00:02:34.791
<b>The skill of flexible thinking is for</b>

57
00:02:34.791 --> 00:02:37.041
<b>managing your initial thoughts about an</b>

58
00:02:37.041 --> 00:02:40.041
<b>emotional situation by learning to think</b>

59
00:02:40.041 --> 00:02:42.375
<b>in a more flexible and balanced way.</b>

60
00:02:43.375 --> 00:02:45.875
<b>You will have options in your mind where</b>

61
00:02:45.875 --> 00:02:47.750
<b>previously your thoughts might have been</b>

62
00:02:47.750 --> 00:02:50.083
<b>very black and white, or you might have</b>

63
00:02:50.083 --> 00:02:51.333
<b>jumped to a conclusion.</b>

64
00:02:54.458 --> 00:02:57.208
<b>The skill of flexible physical sensations</b>

65
00:02:57.208 --> 00:03:00.000
<b>is for learning to tolerate the natural</b>

66
00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:03.250
<b>physical sensations of any emotional</b>

67
00:03:03.250 --> 00:03:05.875
<b>response, raised heart rate, sweaty</b>

68
00:03:05.875 --> 00:03:09.083
<b>palms, tent muscles, tears, and so on.</b>

69
00:03:10.208 --> 00:03:11.500
<b>We'll learn how to become more</b>

70
00:03:11.500 --> 00:03:13.500
<b>comfortable with these natural physical</b>

71
00:03:13.500 --> 00:03:15.416
<b>reactions and be better</b>

72
00:03:15.416 --> 00:03:17.083
<b>able to tolerate them.</b>

73
00:03:19.291 --> 00:03:22.000
<b>This area of the garden called emotion</b>

74
00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:26.291
<b>exposure helps us get closer to and learn</b>

75
00:03:26.291 --> 00:03:28.625
<b>how to stay with your emotions.</b>

76
00:03:30.166 --> 00:03:33.041
<b>If you do that, then difficult emotions</b>

77
00:03:33.041 --> 00:03:36.541
<b>become less of a focus and more helpful</b>

78
00:03:36.541 --> 00:03:38.041
<b>emotions can be a</b>

79
00:03:38.041 --> 00:03:40.375
<b>source of joy in your life.</b>

80
00:03:42.125 --> 00:03:44.833
<b>The skill of flexible behaviour is for</b>

81
00:03:44.833 --> 00:03:47.291
<b>dealing with the emotional urge to behave</b>

82
00:03:47.291 --> 00:03:48.875
<b>in a particular way.</b>

83
00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:52.458
<b>We'll learn to accept the way we feel as</b>

84
00:03:52.458 --> 00:03:56.333
<b>valid, but choose to act in a way that is</b>

85
00:03:56.333 --> 00:03:59.041
<b>more consistent with your long term goals</b>

86
00:03:59.041 --> 00:04:00.666
<b>and personal values.</b>

87
00:04:03.125 --> 00:04:05.416
<b>Next is the part of the garden devoted to</b>

88
00:04:05.416 --> 00:04:06.541
<b>bringing our attention</b>

89
00:04:06.541 --> 00:04:07.875
<b>to the present moment.</b>

90
00:04:09.208 --> 00:04:12.750
<b>This is called mindfulness. Instead of</b>

91
00:04:12.750 --> 00:04:14.750
<b>dwelling on the past or worrying about</b>

92
00:04:14.750 --> 00:04:17.625
<b>the future, you will learn to focus on</b>

93
00:04:17.625 --> 00:04:20.083
<b>what is happening in the here and now,</b>

94
00:04:20.833 --> 00:04:22.250
<b>and approach your reactions</b>

95
00:04:22.250 --> 00:04:24.708
<b>and emotions without judgement.</b>

